## 2. ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

### 2.1 Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Why |
|-----------|-----------|-----|
| Language | **Python 3.11+** | Best CV/ML ecosystem, proven in Prototype 01 |
| UI Framework | **PySide6 (Qt6)** | Professional cross-platform desktop UI, LGPL licensed |
| Video Decoding | **OpenCV (cv2)** | Fast frame extraction, handles all major codecs |
| Pixel Processing | **NumPy** | Array operations for image data |
| Image I/O | **Pillow (PIL)** | PNG/TIFF reading and writing |
| 3D Preview | **PyVistaQt + VTK** | Qt-native 3D widget with built-in orbit/zoom/pan |
| 2D Preview | **QGraphicsView** (Qt) | Built-in zoom/pan for 2D images |
| 3D Export | **trimesh** | OBJ and glTF/GLB export with textures |
| Shot Detection | **PySceneDetect** | Configurable cut detection (Phase 3) |
| Object Detection | **SAM2** | Silhouette segmentation — not just bounding boxes (later add-on) |
| PDF Generation | **ReportLab** | Printable unfold PDFs (Phase 2) |
| Packaging | **PyInstaller** | Standalone .dmg / .exe |

### 2.2 Design Patterns

- **Model-View-Controller (MVC)**: Models (data/state), Views (UI panels), Controllers (processors)
- **QThread Workers**: ALL video processing in background threads. The UI thread never blocks.
- **Signal-Slot**: Qt signals for progress, completion, errors between threads and UI
- **Strategy Pattern**: Each visualization mode is a separate processor class with a common interface
- **Central State Object**: `ProjectState` holds all settings; UI panels observe it and react

### 2.3 Memory & Performance Strategy

**Target workload**: HD 1080p video, 10–60 minutes (18,000–108,000 frames at 30fps).

| Strategy | How it works |
|----------|-------------|
| **Streaming extraction** | Read one frame at a time via OpenCV `cap.read()` loop; never buffer the whole video |
| **Edge-only for void modes** | A 1920×1080 frame has ~6,000 edge pixels vs ~2,000,000 total. Only edges stored in RAM |
| **Frame sampling** | User sets "sampling rate" (every Nth frame). Reduces processed frames proportionally |
| **Preview after export** | 3D preview builds ONLY after all files are written to disk, and ONLY if user opts in |
| **Texture downscaling** | Preview textures capped at 2048×2048 pixels |
| **Memory estimation** | Before generation, estimate memory usage. Warn user if >1GB expected |
| **Disk-based fill mode** | Cuboid Fill writes each full frame to disk as PNG, not RAM |

