### 3.2 Layout Rules

- **Sidebar**: ~280px fixed width, scrollable vertically when controls overflow
- **Preview area**: fills all remaining space, proportionally responsive
- **Scrubber bar**: fixed at bottom of the preview area, always visible when a video is loaded
- **Dark theme**: background #1e1e1e, panels #2b2b2b, text #e0e0e0, accent #e6a817 (amber)
- **Preview tabs**: At top of preview area — "Frame Editor" | "3D Preview" | "2D Preview" — only relevant tabs enabled per mode

### 3.3 Mask Overlay Behavior

The frame preview shows the current video frame. On top of it, a **red semi-transparent mask** is drawn that corresponds to the active mode:

| Mode | Mask shape | Interaction |
|------|-----------|-------------|
| **Slice** | Red line (vertical or horizontal) | Drag line left/right (or up/down). Width corresponds to slit width. |
| **Cuboid** | Red rectangle (inset from frame edges) | Drag any edge inward/outward. Spin boxes in sidebar sync with drag. |
| **Cylinder** | Red circle | Drag center point. Drag circle edge to change radius. |
| **Rings** | Concentric red circles (sparse preview) | Shows which ring corresponds to current frame. Center draggable. |
| **Slit-Tear** | User-drawn colored lines | Free-draw tool. Multiple lines in different colors. Undo support. |

### 3.4 Preview Area States

1. **No video loaded**: Show centered text "Open a video file to begin"
2. **Video loaded, no generation yet**: Show current frame with mask overlay
3. **Generation in progress**: Keep showing frame with mask; progress bar in sidebar
4. **Generation complete, preview enabled**:
   - 3D modes (Cuboid, Cylinder) → switch to 3D preview (orbit/zoom/pan)
   - 2D modes (Slice, Rings, Slit-Tear) → switch to 2D preview (zoom/pan)
5. **User can always toggle back** to frame editor via tab buttons

